## Section 01: Six Major Cascade Events (2024–2026)

Each event crossed $200M in aggregate crypto liquidations within a 4H window. Events are classified by cascade type and assessed against the system's likely 4H signal state at time of event.

---

### Event 1 — August 5, 2024: Yen Carry Trade Unwind
**Type:** Long Squeeze  
**Magnitude:** $1.0B+ total; $420M BTC, $340M ETH  
**Outcome:** Stop-out

Bank of Japan rate hike expectations triggered yen strengthening and unwinding of global carry trades. Crypto treated as high-beta risk-off asset. BTC fell from ~$64K to $54K. Over 275,000 traders liquidated. Largest single liquidation: $27M BTC/USD on Huobi. Fear & Greed Index hit 26. The cascade began on thin weekend liquidity, amplifying the move significantly.

**Signal state:** The 4H EMA would have shown a bullish cross preceding the event given weeks of upward trend. RSI was in the 60–68 range. Any long entry in the 24H preceding the cascade would have been stopped out within 2–3 candles as the yen surge triggered mechanical selling across leveraged positions.

---

### Event 2 — December 5, 2024: Post-$100K ATH Profit-Taking Cascade
**Type:** Long Squeeze  
**Magnitude:** $1.0B+ total; $565M BTC  
**Outcome:** Stop-out

BTC hit $103,900 ATH then plunged to $97,000 within hours. Over-leveraged longs and institutional profit-taking at psychological resistance. This is the one case where RSI overbought filtering would have been protective — the 4H RSI would have been in the 78–82 range at the entry zone, which is above the system's normal entry threshold. If RSI filters were applied correctly, this signal may not have triggered. However, a trailing entry on a "breakout continuation" setup above $100K would have been stopped out.

---

### Event 3 — October 10, 2025: Trump 100% China Tariff — Largest Cascade in History
**Type:** Long Squeeze  
**Magnitude:** $19.16B total — all-time record  
**Outcome:** Stop-out

Trump announced 100% tariffs on Chinese imports after market close Friday. BTC fell from $126K to below $102K (down ~15%), ETH down 12%, SOL down 15%. Perpetual futures OI fell 43% from $217B to $123B. 1.6M traders liquidated. USDe stablecoin depegged to $0.65 on Binance, triggering secondary liquidation waves.

**Signal state:** BTC had been in a clear uptrend for weeks. The 4H EMA would have been bullish. Any long entered in the 48H preceding the announcement would have been stopped out. The critical context: OI was at a record $217B cross-crypto and funding rates had been running at 20–25% annualized for weeks — both signals that should have flagged cascade risk under the proposed filters.

---

### Event 4 — November 20–21, 2025: Post-October Structural Weakness Cascade
**Type:** Long Squeeze (slow-burn)  
**Magnitude:** $2.0B total; $964M BTC  
**Outcome:** Partial (context-dependent)

BTC slid from $120K to $82K over several weeks, with the critical cascade window on Nov 20–21. 396,000 traders liquidated (highest single-day count of 2025). Funding rates fell sharply from -20% to -35%, indicating forced long exits. BlackRock IBIT recorded its largest daily outflow ($523M).

**Signal state:** By Nov 18, the 4H EMA was in confirmed downtrend — system should have been in no-trade or short bias. Any long entered on Nov 15–17 based on a relief-rally signal would have been stopped out within 72 hours. This event is "partial" because a system running correctly with EMA trend filter active would not have entered long.

