### Event 5 — February 1–5, 2026: "Black Sunday II" — Double Liquidation
**Type:** Cascading Double-Liquidation  
**Magnitude:** $2.5B peak day; $12B+ total period  
**Outcome:** Stop-out (long leg); short viable after confirmed break

US-Iran tension spike, Kevin Warsh Fed nomination (hawkish), DXY above 97.5. BTC fell from $80K to near $60K across the window. Feb 5 registered a -6.05σ rate-of-change Z-score — among the fastest single-day crashes in crypto history. BTC futures OI fell from $61B to $49B in one week.

**Signal state:** This was a true double-liquidation event: longs were cascaded down, shorts were temporarily squeezed on recoveries, then a second long cascade resumed. Any 4H long signal in late January would have been stopped out. Any short entered after a confirmed break of $74K support would have been profitable. The system's EMA filter should have indicated no-long bias by Jan 30 based on the trend structure.

---

### Event 6 — September 22, 2025: Fed Tightening Signal — Funding-Rate Cascade
**Type:** Funding-Rate Triggered  
**Magnitude:** $3.62B total; BTC -15%, ETH -20%  
**Outcome:** Stop-out

Following a strong summer rally, Federal Reserve tightening signals triggered collapse of over-leveraged long positions. Positive funding had been extreme for weeks (annualized rates 20–25%), attracting new longs, until the macro catalyst caused rapid reversal.

**Signal state:** This is the cascade type most dangerous to EMA-following systems. The setup looks bullish right up until the unwind. The preceding period featured short squeezes generating false long signals — any long entered during late August would have appeared to be a legitimate momentum continuation trade. This event would not have been blocked by EMA trend filters alone. It requires the funding rate gate (Filter A) to catch it.

