## Section 03: Pre-Trade Filters

### Filter A — Open Interest Elevation + Funding Rate Spike Gate
**Integration recommendation: GO — Integrate as Gate 1C-ii**

**Logic:** Block any long entry when both of the following conditions are simultaneously true in the 4H window preceding signal generation:

- **Condition 1:** BTC or ETH perpetual futures OI is elevated by **>15% above its 30-day rolling average** (CoinGlass OI chart, prior session). Flags the leverage overhang that creates cascade fuel.
- **Condition 2:** Aggregate funding rate (8H period, cross-exchange) is positive and above **>0.05% per 8H** (annualized equivalent ~22%). Flags the regime where long traders are paying a significant premium to hold, indicating overcrowding. Data source: CoinGlass funding rate dashboard or Coinalyze.

**Performance estimate:**
- Events blocked: 4/5 long-squeeze-type cascades
- False positive rate: ~18% (signals blocked with no cascade)
- Estimated R saved across study period: ~4R
- False positive cost: ~0.2R per filtered signal at baseline expectancy

Both the Aug 2024 and Sep 2025 events were preceded by sustained periods where OI was elevated and funding was running hot. In Oct 2025, OI was at an all-time high ($217B cross-crypto) and funding had been averaging 20–25% annualized for weeks. This filter does not block short entries and does not block long entries when only one condition is true.

---

### Filter B — Prior 4H Liquidation Volume Gate
**Integration recommendation: GO — Integrate as Gate 1C-iii**

**Logic:** Block any entry (long or short) when the preceding 4H candle reports BTC or ETH aggregate liquidations exceeding **>$150M in the prior 4H window** (CoinGlass liquidation chart, 4H granularity, same-asset filter). Secondary alert threshold at **>$75M prior 4H** triggers size reduction to 50% of normal risk unit rather than full block.

After two consecutive 4H candles below $50M in liquidations, filters clear and normal gate evaluation resumes.

**Performance estimate:**
- Events blocked: 5/6 cascade events
- False positive rate: ~8% (signals blocked with no cascade)
- Size-reduction days: ~12% of trading days in volatile regimes
- Data source: CoinGlass 4H liquidation view, Coinalyze aggregated liquidation chart

The $150M BTC threshold is set above normal market noise ($30–80M typical elevated-volatility 4H) but below the cascade floor. Once a 4H candle has produced $150M+ in liquidations, the cascade machinery is active — entering a momentum trade into this is entering into mechanical selling pressure that has nothing to do with directional conviction.

