## Section 04: Checklist Integration

**Filter A (OI + Funding Gate):** Integrate as Gate 1C-ii. Insert immediately after existing microstructure gate 1C-i. Operationally: check CoinGlass OI vs. 30-day MA and funding rate snapshot before any long entry. Takes <60 seconds with CoinGlass dashboard already open.

**Filter B (Prior 4H Liquidation Gate):** Integrate as Gate 1C-iii. Check CoinGlass or Coinalyze 4H liquidation volume for the asset being traded before entry. If >$150M: no entry. If $75–150M: reduce position to 50% risk unit. If <$75M: proceed to remaining gates.

**Combined application logic:** Filters A and B are complementary, not redundant. Filter A is a forward-looking leading indicator (elevated OI + high funding = conditions are ripe for cascade). Filter B is a real-time lagging indicator (liquidations already happening = cascade is active). If either triggers, trade is blocked. Clearing both means the entry environment is cascade-neutral.

