## Conclusion

Across six major cascade events from August 2024 through February 2026, the 4H EMA/RSI momentum system would have been stopped out in five of them had entries been taken on technically valid signals. The structural reason is consistent: the system reads price momentum, and cascades generate momentum that is mechanically rather than directionally driven.

The two filters proposed here address this by adding derivatives market structure data as a pre-entry gate. They are not designed to make the system better at predicting cascades — they are designed to make the system avoid entering during the specific market conditions (elevated OI, high funding, active liquidation flow) that correlate with cascade risk.

The combined false positive rate (~10–15% of non-cascade signals blocked when both filters run in parallel) is an acceptable cost relative to the approximately 4–5R in losses avoided across the study period.

The immediate operational implication is to add gates 1C-ii and 1C-iii to the pre-trade checklist before the next live forward-testing session.

